4:
...That's the story my father would
tell me when I couldn't fall asleep.
6:
The story of the champion of the
ocean, Verikion.
9:
He would wear a huge diving suit
and defeat any monster that stood
in his way. He was an unbeatable
hero.
11:
In the story, Verikion was actually
my dad. He kept his identity a secret
from everyone but me.
14:
But I thought it was just a fairy tale.
One he made up just for me.
20:
Real or not, this Verikion sounds like
quite the hero.
24:
Yeah, but now I know he is real! Vriki
really exists!
32:
If Vriki is with me, I feel like I can
handle anything.
37:
I heard that you've been taking Vriki
along with you when you play with
other children... Is that really safe?
42:
Of course. He's not dangerous or
scary! Vriki said so himself.
47:
I mean, as long as you let other
people know he's harmless, I don't
see a problem.
56:
Don't worry—I'll be there too. If Vriki
just stands still and doesn't spook
anyone, we should be fine.
61:
Oh, hi there. Are you on your way
somewhere?
64:
Yeah, to see my dad! He's finally
coming back!
66:
He was off working somewhere in
the west. My mom and I are going to
meet him!
68:
I'm sorry, dear... She didn't mean to
be so inconsiderate.
71:
N-no, ma'am, there's no need to
apologize.
77: It's okay. I'm fine! Vriki says so.
80:
Actually, I'm heading out right now
too.
83: And I'm also going with my dad!
86:
Well... Not exactly, I guess... But I am
going with Vriki!
93:
Your dad, huh... And Vriki is...
Hmm...
111:
Wow, Vriki! They didn't stand a
chance against you!
122:
You promised that you wouldn't get
too close to the front lines! At least
wait until we take the enemies out...
126: But I'm not in any danger.
129:
I have Vriki with me! He can't be
defeated... I'm totally safe.
135:
Don't let your guard down! The next
wave's comin' in fast!
142: Verikion is undefeatable! He's a hero!
159:
I'll be fine! I... I'm with my dad, after
all!
168:
Alk! Nimbus!
It's okay... She's merely fainted.
192:
Wh-what is this power emanating
from him? It doesn't seem to be the
spirits of the dead...
210:
I'm so sorry... This is all my fault. I
was just... so lonely without you...
218:
Alk, you got a good look inside,
right? What'd you see?
223:
I... I honestly have no idea. I definitely
saw something, but... I couldn't tell...
225:
All I know is... There's no way that
thing is her father.
229:
Dad... Don't ever leave me alone
again.
We'll be together forever.
